parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Transmission Oil Leak and Fire Hazard
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission oil leaks can cause a vehicle fire, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission oil leak
burning smell
smoke or flames coming from the transmission area
vehicle catching fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission problems can cause a vehicle fire, which can lead to serious accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission failure
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission
burning smell
smoke or flames coming from the transmission area
vehicle catching fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause a fire, which can lead to a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Unusual noises
such as clunking or grinding
coming from the alternator
smoke or burning smells
visible flames or sparks from the alternator area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the windshield wiper motor can reduce visibility during rain, snow, or other weather conditions, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The windshield wipers do not turn on
the windshield wipers move slowly or erratically
the windshield wipers make a loud noise or grinding sound
the windshield wipers stop working suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A warped brake rotor can cause the vehicle to pulsate or vibrate when the brakes are applied, leading to reduced braking performance and increased stopping distance, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle pulsates or vibrates when the brakes are applied
the brake pedal feels spongy or soft
the brake pedal vibrates or pulsates
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the cruise control system can cause the vehicle to accelerate out of control, leading to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly
the vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
the cruise control system fails to disengage
the vehicle speed increases rapidly without warning.
